            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I have worked on an initial patch that fixes the bug, but it's greatly inspired by the older code that got removed. It is subject to improvements:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/normal.c b/src/nvim/normal.c\r\nindex 7fe646952..71a2e5c19 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/normal.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/normal.c\r\n@@ -1468,6 +1468,21 @@ static void move_tab_to_mouse(void)\r\n   }\r\n }\r\n \r\n+int mouse_has_visual(void)\r\n+{\r\n+  for (char_u *p = p_mouse; *p; ++p)\r\n+    switch (*p) {\r\n+    case 'a':\r\n+        return true;\r\n+      break;\r\n+    case MOUSE_HELP: if (curbuf->b_help)\r\n+        return true;\r\n+      break;\r\n+    default: if (MOUSE_VISUAL == *p) return true; break;\r\n+    }\r\n+  return false;\r\n+}\r\n+\r\n /// Do the appropriate action for the current mouse click in the current mode.\r\n /// Not used for Command-line mode.\r\n ///\r\n@@ -1865,7 +1880,7 @@ bool do_mouse(oparg_T *oap, int c, int dir, long count, bool fixindent)\r\n         if (VIsual_active) {\r\n           jump_flags |= MOUSE_MAY_STOP_VIS;\r\n         }\r\n-      } else {\r\n+      } else if (mouse_has_visual()) {\r\n         jump_flags |= MOUSE_MAY_VIS;\r\n       }\r\n     } else if (which_button == MOUSE_RIGHT) {\r\n@@ -1883,7 +1898,9 @@ bool do_mouse(oparg_T *oap, int c, int dir, long count, bool fixindent)\r\n         }\r\n       }\r\n       jump_flags |= MOUSE_FOCUS;\r\n-      jump_flags |= MOUSE_MAY_VIS;\r\n+      if (mouse_has_visual()) {\r\n+        jump_flags |= MOUSE_MAY_VIS;\r\n+      }\r\n     }\r\n   }\r\n \r\n```\r\n\r\nAt least I have identified where the bug is, it is toggling on `MOUSE_MAY_VIS` where it should not.",
